From 83ce1a7f873581b5cf4608d8abd6cae8ca19a287 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reap-loop <dev@reap-loop.local>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 07:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] pace: 0022 v3 S1-guided rewind -- deep pre-erosion checkpoint
 ring + char-garbage detector + resume mini-warmup

ANCHORED TO THE CANONICAL v2 CHAIN + 0027 + 0028 (base github.com/antirez/ds4
@80ebbc3 + patches/ds4/canonical/ 21 patches -> ds4.c md5 1db4f799, + 0027 +
0028 -> md5 62ed2e71). Applies AFTER 0028; single self-contained patch that
REPLACES the v2 rewind actuator (0022 v1=044b32ce, v2=a88f9dcb). Reconstruction
verified byte-exact against every documented checkpoint before authoring; the
v3 target ds4.c is md5 d4ff85af (562 insertions / 12 hunks over 62ed2e71).

v3 fixes the three MECHANISTIC causes the PIVOTAL K12+rewind experiment
identified for the v2 0/7-on-wide failure
(runs/ds4/20260711_pivotal_k12_rewind/REPORT.md, commit 2c1d92d):

  (1) CHECKPOINT INSIDE THE LOCK. v2 kept ONE rolling snapshot, frozen at ARM;
      in fast-collapse ARM lags the erosion, so the frozen anchor (pos 246)
      already sat past the erosion (char 400) and the lock (char 493) -- rewind
      teleported from-inside-the-lock to inside-the-lock. FIX: a rolling RING of
      DS4_PACE_REWIND_CKPT_DEPTH snapshots at fixed spacing (every EVERY tok);
      at FIRE the OLDEST still-in-window slot is the target, so the anchor
      predates the erosion even when the detector arms late. depth 8 x every 32
      covers ~256 tok of pre-erosion history; depth 1 == the v2 behaviour.

  (2) DETECTOR WITHOUT LEAD. S1 rises only AT the periodic lock, not during the
      erosion, and CALWIN=128 overlaps the collapse -- no lead in the aggressive
      regime. FIX: a CHAR-LEVEL garbage detector (DS4_PACE_REWIND_GARBAGE) that
      sees the erosion BEFORE the lock. It decodes each generated token to bytes
      and folds a per-char non-structural indicator into an EWMA: valid
      HTML/CSS/code interleaves a high density of structural punctuation
      (<>{}[]();:="'/,# digits, whitespace); the pre-lock word-salad
      ('gposcate','finto sfondo','sfchiesto') is bare letters, so the
      non-structural fraction spikes ~a lock-period early. Crossing the
      threshold ARMs the ring early (freezes it pre-erosion) and is an
      independent FIRE source; hysteresis releases it well below threshold so a
      benign prose burst re-opens the rolling ring.

  (3) NO-OP AT RESUME. With K pinned + greedy the v2 rewind was byte-identical
      by construction (same onset logits + same context + same mask => same
      argmax). FIX: DS4_PACE_REWIND_WARMUP -- at resume widen to keep_max (or
      REWIND_KEEP) for a mini-warmup of N tok, THEN re-freeze to the operating K
      that was in force before the rewind. Re-processing the CLEANED context
      with more capacity forces the greedy trajectory to actually diverge, then
      the narrow re-freeze keeps the low-K t/s/VRAM budget. WARMUP=0 keeps the
      v2 permanent-widen behaviour.

Implementation (v3 reduces to v2 when CKPT_DEPTH=1, GARBAGE=0, WARMUP=0):
  - the g->spec_rewind_* GPU frontier buffers become a [DEPTH_MAX][LAYER] ring,
    allocated for rewind_depth slots (DS4_PACE_REWIND_CKPT_DEPTH, clamped
    1..DS4_PACE_REWIND_DEPTH_MAX=16) when DS4_PACE_REWIND=1; free loops over the
    full compile-time ring; snapshot/restore_frontier + save/restore_pace take a
    slot; g_rewind carries a per-slot host checkpoint (logits + full PACE blob +
    mass/rmass/bmass/admit arrays + frontier counters);
  - ds4_pace_rewind_feed_token (both decode loops, next to trace_token_sidecar /
    the actuator) drives the char detector;
  - ds4_pace_rewind_after_eval: warmup countdown (top, runs every token),
    ring-push while quiet, ARM = S1-CUSUM OR garbage-latch, deep-target
    selection at FIRE (oldest in-window slot; rewind_skip{out_of_window} if the
    whole ring aged past the raw-ring slack), ring consumed after a rewind.
    rewind_arm reason distinguishes char_garbage vs s1_cusum_arm; rewind reason
    distinguishes s1_cusum_fire / ngram_airbag / char_garbage.

New env (three headline knobs from the post-mortem; the rest inherited from v2):
  DS4_PACE_REWIND_CKPT_DEPTH (1)  ring depth / pre-erosion coverage
  DS4_PACE_REWIND_GARBAGE   (0.0) char-detector threshold (non-structural EWMA;
                                  <=0 disables); smoke recommendation ~0.80-0.88
  DS4_PACE_REWIND_WARMUP    (0)   resume mini-warmup length in tokens
garbage EWMA alpha is fixed internally (0.04, ~25-char smoothing).

Scope unchanged: correction tier, DS4_PACE_REWIND=0 default, requires DS4_PACE=1
+ DS4_PACE_S1=1. Static-mask greedy CLI + session paths. NOT yet covered:
temp>0 RNG snapshot, MTP-on speculative multi-accept across a rewind, dynamic-
mask relearn exactness under the window. Authored CPU-only (no local gcc):
git apply --check clean on the real chain, brace/paren/bracket balance identical
to base0028 and v2, symbol cross-check clean. Pending pod smoke.

